            "description": "## Update Tour\n\nUpdates an existing tour's details using a partial update. Only the fields provided in the request body will be modified — other fields remain unchanged.\n\n**Method:** `PATCH`  \n**Endpoint:** `{{URL}}api/v1/tours/:id`\n\n---\n\n### Path Parameter\n\n| Parameter | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `id` | The unique identifier of the tour to update. In this request, the tour ID is `6981f19bb94b33f986b3991b`. |\n\n---\n\n### Request Body\n\nThe request body should be a JSON object containing the fields you want to update.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"guides\": [\"6980d0b8404aa98f2308069d\", \"6980dee0ab638ee608711e37\"]\n}\n```\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `guides` | `array of strings` | A list of user IDs representing the tour guides assigned to this tour. Each string is the unique ID of a guide (user) in the system. |\n\n---\n\n### Notes\n\n- This endpoint uses `PATCH`, meaning it performs a **partial update** — only the fields included in the body are changed.\n- The `guides` array replaces the current list of assigned guides for the specified tour.\n- Authentication is required. Include a valid JWT token via the `{{jwt}}` variable in the Authorization header."
