            "description": "## Get All Tours\n\nRetrieves a list of tours filtered by the specified query parameters. This endpoint supports advanced filtering using comparison operators in bracket notation, allowing you to narrow down results based on price, ratings, and other numeric fields.\n\n### Endpoint\n\n```\nGET {{URL}}api/v1/tours\n\n ```\n\n### Query Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Value | Description |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `price[lt]` | `1000` | Returns only tours with a price **less than** 1000 |\n| `ratingsAverage[gte]` | `4.7` | Returns only tours with an average rating **greater than or equal to** 4.7 |\n\n### Filtering Syntax\n\nThis API uses a bracket notation for comparison-based filtering:\n\n- `[lt]` — less than (`<`)\n    \n- `[lte]` — less than or equal to (`<=`)\n    \n- `[gt]` — greater than (`>`)\n    \n- `[gte]` — greater than or equal to (`>=`)\n    \n\nThese operators can be applied to any numeric field (e.g., `price`, `ratingsAverage`, `duration`, `maxGroupSize`) to build flexible, precise queries.\n\n### Example Request\n\n```\nGET {{URL}}api/v1/tours?price[lt]=1000&ratingsAverage[gte]=4.7\n\n ```\n\nThis returns all tours that cost less than **1000** and have an average rating of at least **4.7**."
          },
