            "description": "## Create New Tour\n\nCreates a new tour in the system. This endpoint accepts tour details in the request body and persists the new tour to the database.\n\n---\n\n### Authentication\n\nThis endpoint requires a valid JWT token. Include it as a Bearer token in the `Authorization` header:\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer {{jwt}}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Request Body\n\nSend a JSON object with the following fields:\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `name` | `string` | Yes | The name/title of the tour |\n| `duration` | `number` | Yes | Duration of the tour in days |\n| `maxGroupSize` | `number` | Yes | Maximum number of participants allowed in the group |\n| `difficulty` | `string` | Yes | Difficulty level of the tour. Accepted values: `easy`, `medium`, `difficult` |\n| `price` | `number` | Yes | Price of the tour in the base currency |\n| `summary` | `string` | Yes | A short summary describing the tour |\n| `imageCover` | `string` | Yes | Filename of the cover image for the tour (e.g., `tour-3-cover.jpg`) |\n\n**Example Request Body:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"New Test tour 2\",\n  \"duration\": 1,\n  \"maxGroupSize\": 1,\n  \"difficulty\": \"easy\",\n  \"price\": 200,\n  \"summary\": \"Nice adventure\",\n  \"imageCover\": \"tour-3-cover.jpg\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Responses\n\n- **201 Created** — Tour was successfully created. Returns the newly created tour object.\n- **400 Bad Request** — Validation failed. One or more required fields are missing or invalid.\n- **401 Unauthorized** — Missing or invalid JWT token.\n"
          },
