            "description": "## Delete Tour\n\nDeletes a specific tour from the system using its unique ID.\n\n**Method:** `DELETE`  \n**URL:** `{{URL}}api/v1/tours/69c81561f85c2339878b48d1`\n\n---\n\n### Path Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `69c81561f85c2339878b48d1` | The unique ID of the tour to be deleted. Replace this with the ID of the tour you want to delete. |\n\n---\n\n### Authentication\n\nThis endpoint requires a valid JWT token. The token is read from the `{{jwt}}` variable and should be included in the request headers (e.g., as a `Bearer` token in the `Authorization` header).\n\nMake sure the `jwt` variable is set in your active environment before sending this request.\n\n---\n\n### Expected Behavior\n\n- **Success:** Returns a `204 No Content` or `200 OK` response indicating the tour was successfully deleted.\n- The tour with the specified ID will be permanently removed from the system.\n- If the tour does not exist, the API may return a `404 Not Found` response.\n- If the JWT token is missing or invalid, the API will return a `401 Unauthorized` response."
