            "description": "## Get Top 5 Cheap Tours\n\nRetrieves a pre-filtered list of the **top 5 cheapest tours** available. This is an alias route that automatically applies sorting by price (ascending) and limits the result set to 5 tours, making it a convenient shortcut for displaying budget-friendly options.\n\n### Base URL\n\nThis request uses the `{{URL}}` collection variable as the base URL. Ensure the variable is set in your active environment (e.g., `http://localhost:3000/` or your deployed server URL).\n\n### Endpoint\n\n```\nGET {{URL}}api/v1/tours/top-5-cheap\n```\n\n### Response\n\nReturns a JSON object containing:\n\n- **status** – `\"success\"` if the request was successful\n- **results** – the number of tours returned (up to 5)\n- **data** – an object containing a `tours` array with the top 5 cheapest tour documents, each including details such as name, price, duration, difficulty, and ratings\n\n### Example Response Shape\n\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"success\",\n  \"results\": 5,\n  \"data\": {\n    \"tours\": [\n      {\n        \"name\": \"The Sea Explorer\",\n        \"duration\": 7,\n        \"difficulty\": \"medium\",\n        \"price\": 497,\n        \"ratingsAverage\": 4.8\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Notes\n\n- No authentication or query parameters are required for this endpoint.\n- The results are pre-sorted by price in ascending order and limited to 5 records by the server."
          },
