            "description": "## Get Tours Within Radius\n\nRetrieves all tours located within a specified radius from a given geographic center point. This is useful for finding tours available near a particular location, such as a user's current position or a city center.\n\n---\n\n### URL Structure\n\n```\nGET {{URL}}api/v1/tours/tours-within/:distance/center/:latlng/unit/:unit\n```\n\n### URL Parameters\n\n| Parameter  | Value                                    | Description                                                                 |\n|------------|------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| `distance` | `200`                                    | The radius distance within which to search for tours.                       |\n| `center`   | `44.80855321720493,20.455864096688554`   | The center point of the search area, provided as `latitude,longitude`.      |\n| `unit`     | `km`                                     | The unit of measurement for the distance. Accepted values: `km` or `mi`.   |\n\n---\n\n### Notes\n\n- The `center` parameter must be provided as a comma-separated pair of decimal coordinates in the format `latitude,longitude`.\n- The `distance` value is interpreted in the unit specified by the `unit` parameter (`km` for kilometers, `mi` for miles).\n- The example coordinates (`44.80855321720493, 20.455864096688554`) correspond to a location in **Belgrade, Serbia**.\n- Make sure the `{{URL}}` environment variable is set correctly in your active environment (e.g., `Dev:ExploreNow`) before sending the request.\n- Authentication may be required depending on the API configuration — ensure the appropriate `jwt` token is set in your environment if needed."
