            "description": "## Get Distances to Tour From Point\n\nThis endpoint calculates the distances from a given geographic point (latitude, longitude) to **all available tours**, returning the results in the specified unit of measurement.\n\n---\n\n### URL Structure\n\n```\nGET {{URL}}api/v1/tours/distances/:latlng/unit/:unit\n```\n\n| Segment | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `{{URL}}` | Base URL variable (e.g., `http://localhost:3000/` or your deployed API URL) |\n| `api/v1/tours/distances/` | Base path for the distances resource |\n| `44.80855321720493,20.455864096688554` | The starting geographic point as `latitude,longitude` (decimal degrees) |\n| `unit/km` | The unit of distance measurement — use `km` for kilometers or `mi` for miles |\n\n---\n\n### Path Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Example Value | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `latlng` | `44.80855321720493,20.455864096688554` | Comma-separated latitude and longitude of the reference point |\n| `unit` | `km` | Unit for the returned distances. Accepted values: `km` (kilometers), `mi` (miles) |\n\n---\n\n### Variables\n\n- **`{{URL}}`** — Resolves to the base URL of the API server. This is defined in the active environment (e.g., `Dev:ExploreNow`). Make sure the correct environment is selected before sending the request.\n\n---\n\n### Response\n\nA successful response returns a list of all tours along with the calculated distance from the provided geographic point to each tour's location, expressed in the specified unit.\n\n> **Note:** Ensure the coordinates are valid decimal degree values and that the `unit` parameter is either `km` or `mi`. Invalid values may result in an error response."
