            "description": "## Create New Review on Tour\n\nCreates a new review for a specific tour identified by its tour ID. The review includes a numeric rating and a text comment.\n\n---\n\n### Endpoint\n\n```\nPOST {{URL}}api/v1/tours/:tourId/reviews\n```\n\n| Component | Value |\n|-----------|-------|\n| Base URL | `{{URL}}` |\n| Tour ID (path) | `69c821b77ff7943a90f6022c` |\n\n---\n\n### Authentication\n\nThis request requires a valid JWT token. The token is read from the `{{jwt}}` variable and should be included in the `Authorization` header as a Bearer token:\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer {{jwt}}\n```\n\nMake sure the `jwt` variable is set in your active environment before sending this request.\n\n---\n\n### Request Body\n\nThe request body must be sent as `application/json`.\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `rating` | `number` | Yes | Numeric rating for the tour (e.g., 1–5) |\n| `review` | `string` | Yes | Text content of the review |\n\n**Example:**\n```json\n{\n  \"rating\": 5,\n  \"review\": \"Cool\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Variables Used\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `{{URL}}` | Base URL of the API (e.g., `https://api.example.com/`) |\n| `{{jwt}}` | JSON Web Token used for authentication |\n"
